# Trust Lens — Cursor Rules

## Stack
- React + Vite
- Tailwind CSS v3 (custom colors: base, surface, accent, danger, text-primary, text-muted, text-dim)
- IBM Plex Sans + IBM Plex Mono (Google Fonts)
- Vercel serverless functions in /api/
- Groq API (llama-3.3-70b-versatile) for AI features

## Code style
- Functional React components only, no classes
- useState and useEffect hooks only
- Tailwind classes only — zero inline styles except runtime dynamic values (animationDelay etc)
- CommonJS in /api/ files (module.exports, not export default)
- No TypeScript — plain JavaScript
- Semantic HTML with aria attributes on interactive elements

## Colors (never hardcode hex — use Tailwind tokens)
- Background: bg-base (#0f0f0f)
- Cards: bg-surface (#1a1a1a)
- Accent: text-accent / border-accent (#68FF7D)
- Danger: text-danger (#FF6B6B)
- Primary text: text-text-primary (#f4f4f4)
- Muted text: text-text-muted (#6f6f6f)
- Dim text: text-text-dim (#3f3f3f)

## Security rules
- Never put API keys in frontend code
- All external API calls go through /api/ functions
- Always validate and sanitize input in API routes
- Never log sensitive data

## File structure
/api/          — Vercel serverless functions
/src/          — React components
/public/       — Static assets
App.jsx        — Main component (single file for now)
